<span style="font-weight: bold">Floor repairs to the dojo</span><br>
<span style="line-height: 22px; font-size: 20px; color: red;">(THIS EVENT IS CONCLUDED. ALL MATERIALS RELATING TO IT ARE RETAINED FOR ARCHIVING PURPOSES ONLY.)</span><br><br><br>



(This news is being posted here to serve as documentation and reference for future works on our training area, if needed.)<br><br>

The Makati Sports Club engineering department has repaired two areas with defective flooring in our dojo.<br><br>

1) On the walkway at the edge of the tatami on the left rear area of the dojo: 4ft. X 7in. (Two planks of T&G flooring). Executed 2017 June 25.<br><br>

2) Underneath the mat, on the left edge of the tatami near the storeroom door, and approximately 10 inches forward of the cement pedestal that used to serve as mounting for the now-removed plexiglass wall. (Approx. 20in. X 3.5in.) Executed 2017 June 28.<br><br>




